    <para id="import-auto-id1172265676696">(12) implies that whenever the incident light has a frequency equal the natural frequency ω<sub>0</sub> resonance occurs and the incident light is completely absorbed by the medium as dissipative absorption.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1172265488472"> From (9):</para>
